column9: The Center for BRCA Research is a team housed within the Helen Diller Family Comprehensive Cancer Center (HDFCCC) whose mission is to provide a central resource for families with cancer related mutations to receive personalized care and planning for their long-term health and well-being. Our expert team of oncologists, scientists, and genetic counselors provide exceptional care for a sensitive patient population while executing a wide variety of research projects working toward the advancement of precision medicine. The Center for BRCA Research is seeking an ambitious Clinical Research Coordinator to provide oversight of multiple clinical trial projects aimed at understanding cancer etiology, developing diagnostic tests for early detection, and advancing novel therapeutics.
